2.Method Overriding
----------
-->the method overriding occurs when a child class provides its own implementation
of a method already defined in its parent class...
eg:-
class animal:
    def sound(self):
        print("animals make sounds")
class dog(animal):
    def sound(self):
        print("dogs barks")
d=dog()
d.sound()

